description: For sale is a 2012 Chaparral 244 Xtreme. For those who don't know what this boat is, it's a perfect combination of family entertainer (14 passenger!!) and extreme ski boat. It's powered by a 350 Mag and mated to a twin prop stainless steel Bravo 3. The onboard head has only been used as storage. Not that you'll be lacking in the storage area as there is space under each front seat as well as seating in the rear. There is also a ton of space in the floorboard for ski's, wakeboard, fishing equipment, etc. The wakeboard racks are handy when out on the water to make retrieving them quick and easy. There are 2 built in coolers (one in front and one in the rear) as well as an onboard sink and 10 gallons of fresh water capacity. The sound system sounds great turned up when your skier is in tow. I just replaced both batteries, both struts on the engine hatch, and put 5 new tires on the trailer. This boat has only seen the fresh water of the midwest and has been stored in heated storage it's whole life. Are you ready for the best part? There are less than 30 hours on this vessel!! We don't use it enough to justify another winter of storage. Do your homework. The KBB suggested list price is north of $90,000 and average retail still above $60,000. You won't find another 2012 Xtreme or newer less than $65,000 and most of those close have double and triple the hours. This is being listed and priced to allow it to move before winter and let me start looking for a replacement next spring. Email with any questions. I'll respond within 24 hours.
